@page "/docs/motion-value"

<PageTitle>MotionValue — BlazorMotion</PageTitle>

<div class="breadcrumb">Docs / <span>MotionValue</span></div>
<h1>MotionValue</h1>
<p><code>MotionValue&lt;T&gt;</code> is a reactive, frame-accurate value container. Subscribe to it to drive custom animations, derived values, and side effects outside of the standard <code>&lt;Motion&gt;</code> lifecycle.</p>

<h2>Create a MotionValue</h2>
<pre><code>@@inject IMotionValueFactory MVFactory

@@code {
    MotionValue&lt;double&gt; _x = default!;

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        _x = MVFactory.Create(0.0);
        _x.OnChange += v =&gt; Console.WriteLine($"x changed to {v}");
    }
}</code></pre>

<h2>Reading and writing</h2>
<pre><code>double current = _x.Current;
_x.Set(100.0);</code></pre>

<h2>Derived values</h2>
<p>Create a value that transforms another value:</p>
<pre><code>// opacity = 1 - (x / 200)
var opacity = _x.Derived(v =&gt; Math.Clamp(1 - v / 200.0, 0, 1));</code></pre>

<h2>Scroll-linked MotionValue</h2>
<p>Combine with <code>ScrollTracker</code> to drive values from scroll position:</p>
<pre><code>@@inject ScrollTracker Scroll

MotionValue&lt;double&gt; _scrollY = default!;

protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender)
{
    if (firstRender)
    {
        _scrollY = MVFactory.Create(0.0);
        await Scroll.TrackAsync(info =&gt;
        {
            _scrollY.Set(info.ScrollY);
        });
    }
}</code></pre>

<h2>MotionValue API</h2>
<table class="prop-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Member</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td>Current</td><td>The current value.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Set(value)</td><td>Update value and notify subscribers.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>OnChange</td><td>Event fired on each value change.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Derived(transform)</td><td>Returns a new MotionValue derived from this one.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Dispose()</td><td>Unsubscribes and cleans up.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<div class="callout callout-tip">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> MotionValues update synchronously within the animation frame loop, keeping them perfectly in sync with C# WASM animations.
</div>
